// App Store ID configuration — template.
//
// COPY this file to `Tuist/AppStore.xcconfig` (gitignored) and fill in the
// real numeric App Store Connect app id for whichever app you're building.
// The real file must NEVER be committed.
//
// On a fresh clone:
//   cp Tuist/AppStore.xcconfig.example Tuist/AppStore.xcconfig
//   # then edit Tuist/AppStore.xcconfig and replace the value below with the
//   # real ASC app id for the app you're building (or leave the fake value
//   # for sandbox/debug verification — Share App / Write a Review rows
//   # render with it, they just won't resolve to a real storefront listing).
//   mise exec -- tuist generate
//
// Real ASC app ids are NOT documented here — they live in the project's
// private memory (`asc-api-credentials`) and in `secrets/.env`
// (`ASC_APP_ID_SUDOKU` / `ASC_APP_ID_MINESWEEPER`, shared with ASCRegister).
// Ask the project owner if you need them.
//
// For CI (Xcode Cloud): no manual setup needed. The following env vars must
// be defined in ASC → Xcode Cloud → Workflow → Environment Variables (marked
// Secret), one per workflow / app:
//
//   SUDOKU_APP_STORE_ID
//   MINESWEEPER_APP_STORE_ID
//
// `ci_scripts/ci_post_clone.sh` reads them and writes
// `Tuist/AppStore.xcconfig` before `tuist generate` runs, selecting the
// right value per workflow (mirrors AdMob.xcconfig's §3.1b).
//
// The value below is an obviously-fake 10-digit id — safe to commit. Info.plist
// substitution leaves it in place until a real xcconfig is rendered; the
// shared SettingsUI hides the Share App / Write a Review rows whenever the
// resolved id is missing or still the unresolved `$(APP_STORE_ID)` token.

APP_STORE_ID = 0000000000
